50|$|In 1986, {{a former}} technician, Mordechai Vanunu, at the Israeli nuclear {{facility}} near Dimona revealed {{information about the}} Israeli nuclear <b>weapon</b> <b>program</b> to the British press, confirming widely held notions that Israel had an advanced and secretive nuclear <b>weapons</b> <b>program</b> and stockpile. Israel has never acknowledged or denied having a <b>weapons</b> <b>program,</b> and Vanunu was abducted and smuggled to Israel, where he was tried in camera and convicted of treason and espionage.|$|R
